</taxonomicName>
specimens, the authors also collected males and females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kondratieff and Kirchner" authorityName="Kondratieff and Kirchner" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puttmanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">P. puttmanni</emphasis>
Kondratieff and Kirchner
</taxonomicName>
(
<specimenCount box="[1230,1269,868,892]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" type="male">6 ♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[1282,1320,868,892]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" type="female">3 ♀</specimenCount>
) a new state record for NC (Kondratieff et al. 1995). Additionally, 
<emphasis box="[971,1110,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Newman" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[971,1106,937,961]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Acroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abnormis">A. abnormis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Stark and Ray" authorityName="Stark and Ray" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Helopicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bogaloosa">
<emphasis box="[1120,1334,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Helopicus bogaloosa</emphasis>
